Subject: Re: [T2] air scoops


> On Wed, 17 Jul 2002 Gunnys(-at-)aol.com wrote:
>
> > I was thinking of purchasing a pair of aftermarket air scoops  for my 71
> > westy, i was just wondering if they are worth it, ie.. has anyone used
these
> > and seen significant results in cooling? my bus doesnt overheat now,  it
was
> > just a nice preventative maintnance idea for the summer.. any input and
past
> > experiences would be appreciated .. thanks.. peace.. scott 71 vesty
>
> Air scoops will do nothing for a properly maintained bus.  They _may_
> lower temperatures in a bus with missing engine bay seals or other air
> leaks into the engine bay.
>
> Make sure your engine bay seals and tin are present and correct.  This
> will yield much better results than a tack-on!
>

These scoops will actually RAISE temps at slow speeds, since the purpose of
the vents is to allow hot air to escape, not to induct cool air.  I would
warn against them.

